# Frontend Rules (Next.js + React)

## Architecture

- **Routing**: Next.js App Router (`app/` directory)
- **Styling**: TailwindCSS + shadcn/ui components
- **State**: React hooks (useState, useReducer) + custom hooks
- **API calls**: Centralized in `lib/` utilities

## File Naming

- `page.tsx` — Route pages (App Router convention)
- `layout.tsx` — Route layouts
- `loading.tsx` — Loading states
- `error.tsx` — Error boundaries
- `components/*.tsx` — Reusable UI components
- `hooks/use-*.ts` — Custom React hooks
- `lib/*.ts` — Utility functions, API services
- `types/*.ts` — TypeScript type definitions

## Conventions

- Use functional components only — no class components
- Use `"use client"` directive only when needed (event handlers, hooks, browser APIs)
- Default to Server Components for data fetching
- Use `cn()` utility (from shadcn) for conditional classNames
- API base URL: `http://localhost:4001` (backend)
- Use TypeScript strict types — avoid `any`
- Component props should be typed with interfaces
- Use named exports for components

## Commands

```bash
cd frontend
npm run dev      # Dev server (port 4000)
npm run build    # Build
npm test         # Run tests
```
